author: 滇西小哥 Dianxi Xiaoge
description:
※Click "cc" on the lower right menu to choose your subtitle language.

It may not be easy to travel across China with family, but tasting mooncakes and festive specialties from every region during Mid-Autumn is wonderfully simple. This year, we made a few representative mooncakes and also gathered local delicacies from all over the country. When they were all placed together on the map, my family sighed with emotion: truly, China’s bounty is vast, and every place has its own unique flavor.
Wishing everyone a joyful Mid-Autumn Festival, filled with peace and good health. 

Hello, everyone! I am Dianxi Xiaoge, a Yunnan native. If you enjoy my videos, please keep subscribing to my channel. I'll continue to share my life and Yunnan-styled food in my uploads. Wish you have a happy life and enjoy tasty food every day
